               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Filkǝsyos, Book of Philoxenus of Mabbogh: 243 questions and answers
                     (fols. 7r-123vb)
 - Table of contents: 243 titles of questions (fols.
                     7r-12v)
 
 Additiones 1-4.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="7r" to="123vb"/>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1399Filkes">Filkǝsyos</title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="7r" to="12v"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1399Filkes#Content">Table of contents: 243 titles of questions</title>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <note>- The text consists of a series of questions asked by monks (beginning
                        with ይቤሉ: አኃው) and answers given by an “interpreter” (starting with ይቤ:
                        መተርጕም). The questions are numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  
               </msContents>
