                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="1va" to="6vb"/>
                           <locus from="126va" to="127va"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Treatise on love to God and people, and on
                              guarding the faith, addressed to monks (unidentified).</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus> መቅደም፡ ኵሉ፡ አፍቅሮ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ አምላክከ፡ በኵሉ፡
                              ልብከ፡ ወበኵሉ፡ ነፍስከ፡...</q>
                           <note> The text continues from <locus target="#6vb">6vb</locus> into <locus target="#126va">126va</locus>
                          ; it has been corrected in a contemporary hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="124ra" to="126ra"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText"> 
                              <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5625TergSenaFet">Tǝrgʷāme śǝna fǝṭrat “Commentary on the Beauty of
                              Creation”</title>
                           </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#124ra"/> ትርጓሜ: ኦሪት፡ ብሂል፡ ፍትሕ፡ ወሥርዐት: ወዜና፡
                              ይትበሃል፡…</q>
                           
                           <note> The text is written in a hand which is contemporary and similar to
                              the main hand. It has been checked for errors and corrected by another
                              hand. For a similar text s. Mss. MAKM-014 and THMR-018. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#126ra">f. 126ra-va</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Excerpt from the <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2709Matthew">Gospel of Matthew</title> (Mt. 5: 1-11).</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#127va">f. 127va-vb</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2736RepCh20">Malkʾa Śǝllāse (“Image of Trinity”)</title>. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#127va">127va</locus>: አልብየ፡ ባእደ፡ ዘእንበሌክሙ፡ አምላከ፤ አብል፡
                              አንሰ፡ በልብየ: ነግሐ: ወሠርከ። ሥሉስ: ቅዱስ፡ ዘአልብክሙ፡ ተውሰከ። በሉኒ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ሰረይነ፡ ለከ፡
                              ኃጢአተ፡ ኵሎ፡ ዘገበርከ፡…</q>
                           
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work, ፊልክስዮስ, and the internal number
                           of the monastic library (250) are written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>. </item>  
                        <item xml:id="e2">- Tamallas-sign, in the shape of a cross,
                           indicating the place where the omission written in the margin, in a
                           secondary hand, belongs: <locus target="#30vb">30vb</locus> l.12.</item>  
                        <item xml:id="e3"> -
                           Corrections over erasure, in the main hand: e.g., fols. 13ra, 14va,
                           16rab, 21vb, 23vab, 33rab, 37va, 49va, 60va, 77ra, 97va, 109rab.</item>  
                        <item xml:id="e4"> -
                           Erasures marked with two thin lines: <locus target="#15ra">15ra</locus>,
                              15va, 21vb, 22ra, 45ra, 55ra, 66ra, 106vb, 107ra.</item>  
                        <item xml:id="e5"> - Erasures: 14vb,
                           17ra, 26va, 28va, 91rb, 94va, 109vb.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">Shelfmark C3–IV-250 on f. 1r</item>
                        
                     </list>
